Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @Panko Breadcrumbs{10g} and @Water{2%tbsp} into a #bowl{}. Add the @Baharat Spice Mix{1%tsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, add the @Beef Mince{240%g} and mix with your hands until combined. Shape into 4 sausage shapes per person. Flatten to make koftas and pop onto a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Peel the @Garlic Clove{1} and pop into a square of foil with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and scrunch to enclose it. Pop the garlic parcel on a #baking tray{}. Bake the garlic on the top shelf of your oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over a medium high heat. Once hot add the koftas and fry until browned all over and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, pop the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml} into a large bowl and add a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix to combine. Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}(halved) and pop into the bowl with the dressing. Trim the root from the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}(trimmed) then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Set aside - we'll add to the dressing just before serving.

Pop the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{49.5%g} in a bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir to combine. Once the garlic is cooked, remove from the oven. Carefully remove the garlic from the foil, pop on a #cutting board{} and mash with a #fork{}. Stir into the yoghurt. Once the garlic is out of the oven, pop the @Plain Naans{2} on the baking tray, drizzle with @olive oil{drizzle}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until starting to go golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Just before serving, add the baby gem to the tomatoes and toss to combine. Serve the naans with the salad on top, the koftas divided between the naans and a drizzle of roasted garlic yoghurt. Enjoy!